    Three passages moving from anticipation through disappointment to liberation:

    Passage 1: Back at the facility after the journey. Time passes (couple weeks?). Kira and plants working on survival challenges, applying what they learned during the journey. Things are actually going pretty well—better cooperation, better understanding. But still waiting for Elder Heartwood's response as the "real" answer.

    Passage 2: Elder Heartwood's response arrives! Plants gather ceremonially to receive the wisdom. Reading the response—building anticipation—then the crushing realization it's completely inadequate. Fundamental category error makes it clear Elder Heartwood doesn't understand the question at all. Collective disappointment and confusion.

